The paper deals with sparse recovery guarantees for a greedy algorithm in the context of continuous parametric dictionaries, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Hilbert spaces and inner products also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
